query Parameters

string

OrderBy is a comma separated value to define sorting. e.g 'name,CreateConfigd_time DESC'. The values are separated by space, '{column} {ASC/DESC}'. These are the values that are sortable: none

CreateConfig creates an automation config from the specified input

CreateConfigs creates an automation config from the specified input

Authorizations:
API_Keys
Request Body schema: application/json

CreateConfigRequest is the information provided when creating an automation config.

cloud_vault_id
string

The ID of the Cloud Vault to be used during automation.

cron_timer
string

Frequency of the automation represented as a cron time.

description
string

The description of the automation.

enabled
boolean

Is the automation enabled?

end_date_time
string <date-time>

Optional date the automation task will stop being executed automatically.

name
string

The name of the automation.

start_date_time
string <date-time>

Is the date to start automatically running the automation task.

Array of objects (Automations.AutomationStep)

Ordered automation steps of the automation.

timezone_identifier
string

The Timezone Identifier you want the automation to be scheduled in e.g. 'Europe/London', 'America/New_York' and more https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones

https://infosum.github.io/api/v2/automations/configs

Create a new Cloud Vault.

Create a Cloud Vault to hold data and connect to a bunker.

Authorizations:
API_Keys
Request Body schema: application/json
description
string

Description is an optional description given to this Cloud Vault.

name
required
string

Name is the display name given to this Cloud Vault.

region
required
string (CloudVaults.Region)
Default: "UNKNOWN"
Enum: "UNKNOWN" "AWS_EU_WEST_2" "AWS_US_EAST_1" "IBM_EU_CENTRAL_1" "AWS_EU_CENTRAL_1" "AWS_AP_SOUTHEAST_2"

Region enumerates the supported cloud providers and locations.

  • UNKNOWN: UNKNOWN means the region has not been defined.
  • AWS_EU_WEST_2: AWS_EU_WEST_2 means AWS Europe (London).
  • AWS_US_EAST_1: AWS_US_EAST_1 means AWS US East (N. Virginia).
  • IBM_EU_CENTRAL_1: IBM_EU_CENTRAL_1 means IBM MZR EU Central (Frankfurt).
  • AWS_EU_CENTRAL_1: AWS_EU_CENTRAL_1 means AWS Europe (Frankfurt).
  • AWS_AP_SOUTHEAST_2: AWS_AP_SOUTHEAST_2 means AWS Asia Pacific (Sydney)

Responses

https://infosum.github.io/api/v2/cloud_vaults

Creates a Sigma dataset.

Creates a Sigma dataset.

Authorizations:
API_Keys
Request Body schema: application/json

CreateDatasetRequest is the input used by the CreateDataset rpc.

dataset_type
string (Datasets.DatasetType)
Default: "DATASET_TYPE_INVALID"
Enum: "DATASET_TYPE_INVALID" "DATASET_TYPE_INSIGHT" "DATASET_TYPE_IDENTITY"

DatasetType gives the dataset type, insight or identity.

  • DATASET_TYPE_INVALID: Invalid is used when no other enum applies.
  • DATASET_TYPE_INSIGHT: Insight is for insight datasets.
  • DATASET_TYPE_IDENTITY: Identity is for identity (activation) datasets.
description
string

Description is a user defined description for the dataset. Description has a max length of 1000 characters.

object (Datasets.DatasetExpiration)

DatasetExpiration contains information about how a dataset should expire.

private_id
string

PrivateId is the name of the dataset visible only within the owner company, used for querying. PrivateIDs can only contain upper and lower case letter and numbers with a minimum length of 1, and a maximum length of 17.

public_name
string

PublicName is the name of the dataset as seen by other companies with permission to the dataset. PublicNames can only contain alphanumeric (ascii) characters, including dash, underscore and spaces with a max length of 100 and a minimum length of 1.

region
string (Datasets.Region)
Default: "UNKNOWN"
Enum: "UNKNOWN" "AWS_EU_WEST_2" "AWS_US_EAST_1" "IBM_EU_CENTRAL_1" "AWS_EU_CENTRAL_1" "AWS_AP_SOUTHEAST_2"

Region enumerates the supported cloud providers and locations.

  • UNKNOWN: UNKNOWN means the region has not been defined.
  • AWS_EU_WEST_2: AWS_EU_WEST_2 means AWS Europe (London).
  • AWS_US_EAST_1: AWS_US_EAST_1 means AWS US East (N. Virginia).
  • IBM_EU_CENTRAL_1: IBM_EU_CENTRAL_1 means IBM MZR EU Central (Frankfurt).
  • AWS_EU_CENTRAL_1: AWS_EU_CENTRAL_1 means AWS Europe (Frankfurt).
  • AWS_AP_SOUTHEAST_2: AWS_AP_SOUTHEAST_2 means AWS Asia Pacific (Sydney)

Create a Destination

Creates a Destination.

Authorizations:
API_Keys
Request Body schema: application/json

CreateDestinationRequest is the input to the CreateDestination method.

object (Exports.Destination)

Destination is the information required to define destinations.

object (Exports.AirbyteConnector)

AirbyteConnector is the information required to define a destination pushing using airbyte.

connector_type
string (Exports.ConnectorType)
Default: "CONNECTOR_TYPE_INVALID"
Enum: "CONNECTOR_TYPE_INVALID" "S3_ACCESS_KEYS" "PUBMATIC" "S3_CROSS_ACCOUNT" "SFTP" "GCS" "FACEBOOK" "DV360_PAIR" "S3_ACCESS_KEYS_PAIR" "S3_CROSS_ACCOUNT_PAIR" "SFTP_PAIR" "DV360_CUSTOMER_MATCH" "AIRBYTE" "TRADEDESK"

ConnectorType is the types of authentication used by a destination.

  • S3_ACCESS_KEYS: S3_ACCESS_KEYS indicates the destination is targeting S3 and using access/secret keys for authentication.
  • PUBMATIC: PUBMATIC indicates the destination is targeting PubMatic.
  • S3_CROSS_ACCOUNT: S3_CROSS_ACCOUNT indicates the destination is targeting S3 and assuming an iam role for authentication.
  • SFTP: SFTP indicates the destination is targeting a sftp server.
  • GCS: GCS indicates indicates the destination is targeting Google Cloud Platform for authentication.
  • FACEBOOK: FACEBOOK indicates the destination is targeting Facebook.
  • DV360_PAIR: DV360_PAIR indicates the destination is targeting DV360 using PAIR encryption.
  • S3_ACCESS_KEYS_PAIR: S3_ACCESS_KEYS_PAIR indicates the destination is targeting S3 using access/secret keys for authentication and using PAIR encryption.
  • S3_CROSS_ACCOUNT_PAIR: S3_CROSS_ACCOUNT_PAIR indicates the destination is targeting S3 assuming an iam role for authentication and using PAIR encryption.
  • SFTP_PAIR: SFTP_PAIR indicates the destination is targeting a SFTP server for authentication and using PAIR encryption.
  • DV360_CUSTOMER_MATCH: DV360_CUSTOMER_MATCH indicates the destination is targeting DV360 Customer Match.
  • AIRBYTE: AIRBYTE indicates the destionation is targeting the airbyte exporter.
  • TRADEDESK: TRADEDESK indicates the destination is targeting trade desk
description
string

Description is an optional description given to this destination.

object (Exports.DV360Connector)

Dv360Connector is the information required to define a destination pushing to DV360.

object (Exports.DV360Connector)

Dv360Connector is the information required to define a destination pushing to DV360.

object (Exports.FacebookConnector)

List files

List available files with any metadata

Authorizations:
API_Keys
path Parameters
cloud_vault_id
required
string

CloudVaultId is the id of the Cloud Vault to list files from.

path
required
string.+

Path is the path within the cloud vault which has been requested. This will often be blank (no path = list the entire cloudvault), but could also be the path of a single file or directory.

query Parameters
pagination.page
integer <int32>

Page is the page to view.

pagination.per_page
integer <int32>

PerPage is the number of items per page.

order_by
string

OrderBy is a comma separated value to define sorting. e.g 'name,created_time DESC'. The values are separated by space, '{column} {ASC/DESC}'. These are the values that are sortable: name size created_date_time (in RFC3339 format) metadata.updated_date_time (in RFC3339 format) metadata.origin.task_id metadata.origin.task_type metadata.origin.properties

filter
string

Filter is a string containing logic that can specify a restricted set of Files to be returned. e.g. name co 'Test' or name co 'Acme'. These are the supported fields for filtering:

name size created_date_time (in RFC3339 format) metadata.origin.task_type metadata.origin.task_id metadata.updated_date_time (in RFC3339 format) metadata.hidden metadata.resource_type metadata.origin.properties.{property_name} (dynamic filtering based on the properties)

Responses

https://infosum.github.io/api/v2/files/{cloud_vault_id}/{path}

List Global Schema Keys.

List global schema keys

Authorizations:
API_Keys
query Parameters
pagination.page
integer <int32>

Page is the page to view.

pagination.per_page
integer <int32>

PerPage is the number of items per page.

order_by
string

OrderBy is a comma seperated value to define sorting. e.g 'name,created_time DESC' The values are seperated by space, '{column} {ASC/DESC}'

The following values are permitted: name

filter
string

Filter is a string containing logic that can specify a restricted set of Cloud Vaults to be returned. e.g. name co 'Test' or name co 'Acme'

The following values are permitted: name

category_ids
Array of strings <int64>

CategoryIds is the list of Category IDs that are available in the current Category assignment and specifies what keys should be returned.

type
Array of strings
Items Enum: "TYPE_INVALID" "INT64" "UINT64" "DOUBLE" "TEXT" "BOOLEAN" "BYTES" "INT64RANGE" "TEXTARRAY" "INT64ARRAY"

Type describes the data type assigned to a given category.

  • INT64: INT64 is the signed 64-bit integer type.
  • UINT64: UINT64 is the unsigned 64-bit integer type.
  • DOUBLE: DOUBLE is the floating point type.
  • TEXT: TEXT is the string type.
  • BOOLEAN: BOOLEAN is the boolean type.
  • BYTES: BYTES is the bytes type.
  • INT64RANGE: INT64RANGE is the range of signed 64-bit integers type.
  • TEXTARRAY: TEXTARRAY is the text array type.
  • INT64ARRAY: INT64ARRAY is the int64 array type.
